CARIBBEAN VILLAS' VIEW. After studying villa architecture and designs throughout Italy, Amorosa’s owners decided to build an 18th century Italian villa in Peter Bay, and after years of planning and construction, Amorosa was completed in January of 2008. You first glimpse the Mediterranean influence as you drive through the gated entrance and look up at what could be a Tuscan hillside home. But when you step inside Amorosa you see the full range of understated elegance that is the hallmark of a classic Italian villa.
Some of these classic features include; deeply veined Italian marble floors, 4 inch thick marble slabs used for countertops, the abundant use of stonework, antique brick and coral stone, Bellagio finished walls, 9 foot tall Borano mahogany doors, custom built mahogany cabinets, stairs, and windows, arched walls supported by Doric columns, hand built copper lights, and terra cotta Italian roof tiles.
