1. Water sport
. all kind of watersport, the most exciting is diving at Cap Dramont (5 km): living corals, rich fauna and flora, "The little town" of Jacques Cousteau;
. yachting - 5 yachting harbours with rental stations;
. sailing;
2. Ordinary sport
. tennis - 3 tennis courts in Agay at 3 km, 2 tennis courts in Saint-Raphael at 12 km;
. golf - 3 golf courses in Valescure at 8 km (one of them is the oldest course on continent), 1 course is in Agay/Cap Esterel at 5 km, 1 in Mandelieu at 15 km;
3. Mountains sport
. one of the most extraordinary activity is riding in The Esterel-Mountains. You can also rent a mountain bike instead of the hourse;
. people who search for extreme sensations can try paragliding from Cap Dramont;
. you can also try free climbing on Cap Dramont and in the Esterel Mountains.
4. Vineyards
South Rhone region, where the villa lies, is rich of vineyards where are produced such well known vines like Chateauneuf-du-Pape, Cotes-du-Rhone, Gigondas, Coteaux du Tricastin, Vacqueras and many others. Here you can take a trip to the vine castles, meet with makers of your favourite one, make a vine and the cheese of the region tasting. That will definitely stay in your memory as the one of the most exiting thing made in France.
5. Restaurants
Indisputably, one of modern France's greatest treasures is its rich cuisine. French cuisine is considered to be one of the world's most refined and elegant styles of cooking, and is renowned for both its classical and provincial styles. Many of the world's greatest chefs, such as Taillevent, La Varenne, Careme, Escoffier, or Bocuse were masters of French cuisine. Naturally there are many great restaurant famous not only by cuisine but also by spectacular atmosphere and special French style. Most of them lies just on the Mediterranean sea coast with a fantastic view to the blue like a sky water, palms and extraordinary French landscape.
6. Shopping
Fashion - that's what France is famous for. Here in Cannes, Saint-Tropez and Monaco, streets are teeming with stores of the most famous designers, such as Dior, Channel, Rolex, Gucci and millions of others. Here you can find the most unique and unitary products as well as souvenirs of the province.
7. Night life
In such towns like Cannes, Monaco, St. Tropez and many others life is humming in fool speed also after midnight. Here you can find a big variety of entertainment like bars, discos, night clubs, casino and so on. Dance on the beach or glass of exotic drink in a cosy atmosphere - is just a matter of your chose. Indisputably, this is a paradise for ones who love parties.8. Cannes film festival
Cannes is the favourite holidays place of the movie starts from all over the world. Come to Cannes film festival and make you dream come truth - see famous actors, singers and other standing just next to you.
Legendary Cannes lies just 20 km from the villa.
9. Monaco
Monaco - the town of total exclusivity, the place for VIP. Take a trip over there (80 km) and visit one of the most famous casino in the world sarounded by the newest models of the cars like Bently, Aston martin, Ferari, Masarati, Royals rois and millions of other. Make a game of your life in the most luxurious casino.

